Here we define a new subclass of block graphs called ${\operatorname{clique-path}}$ graphs. 
\begin{definition}\label{def:cpgraph}
A clique-path graph $G$ is the union $P\cup C_1 \cup \cdots \cup C_r$
where $P$ is a simple path on the vertices $\{v_0,\ldots,v_\ell\}$ 
and $C_1, \ldots, C_r$ are cliques such that
\begin{enumerate}


  \item $|C_i| \geq 3$ for all $i$;
  \item $C_i \cap C_j \subset P$ and $|C_i \cap C_j| \leq 1$ for
	every $i \neq j$;
  \item $|C_i \cap P| = 1$.
\end{enumerate}
\end{definition}
